  "description": [
    "Bainbridges First Sea Trials Successful USS Bainbridge the worlds first nuclearpowered guded mis sile frigate has successfully com pleted her first sea trials Steam ing 570 miles fully meeting all trial requirements Bainbridge burned less than five ounces of uranium Bainbridge put to sea on 1 Sept from Bethlehem Steel Com pany Quincy Mass Shipyard Some of the tests made included designed full power and demon strating her ability to go from full speed ahead to emergency astern HighSpeed Endurance Bainbridge is powered by two pressurized water nuclear power Art Classes For Adults Children Set The winter schedule for art classes has been announced by the Special Services Department The classes which will again be taught by Ed Connelly will be held in Mr Connellys studio at 67 Coggeshall Ave The new schedule for adult painting and drawing classes calls for sessions to be held each Thursday Hours will be from 1090 1430 and 1900 2200 The first class will be convened on 20 Sept Childrens Classes Childrens classes are scheduled for Saturday from 10001200 and 12301500 First class is slated for Saturday 22 Sept Registration for these classes will commence 18 and 19 Sept Personnel desiring further infor mation"
